The High Court has granted Norma Mngoma's application on an urgent basis. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - The High Court in Pretoria has ruled that Norma Mngoma's arrest was unlawful. Judge Cassim Sardiwalla has ordered that all information removed from her devices be restored. READ: Gigaba Saga: Focus on relationship with the Guptas Last year her estranged husband, former Home Affairs minister Malusi Gigaba, laid charges against her for allegedly damaging a Mercedes G wagon. She was then arrested by the Hawks.